        "created_at": "2018-11-30T16:17:55.562Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hey there -</p>\n<p>I updated my client libraries from 5.2 to 6.0 but now I can\u2019t seem to communicate with my cluster. Is this expected behavior? I\u2019m able to connect to the cluster on any other client that\u2019s using the 5.2 library.</p>\n<pre><code>$ fdbcli\nUsing cluster file `fdb.cluster'.\n\nWARNING: One or more of the processes in the cluster is incompatible with this version of fdbcli.\n\nThe database is unavailable; type `status' for more information.\n\nWelcome to the fdbcli. For help, type `help'.\nfdb&gt; status\n\nWARNING: One or more of the processes in the cluster is incompatible with this version of fdbcli.\n\nUsing cluster file `fdb.cluster'.\n\nCould not communicate with a quorum of coordination servers:\n  10.49.38.10:4500  (unreachable)\n  10.49.38.23:4500  (unreachable)\n  10.49.38.36:4500  (unreachable)\n  10.49.38.52:4500  (unreachable)\n  10.49.38.72:4500  (unreachable)</code></pre>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
        "updated_at": "2018-11-30T16:17:55.562Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
